e. Calypso) <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἥ με . . ἐφίλει τε καὶ ἔτρεφεν</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:7:256\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">7.256</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τίς ἂν φιλέοντι μάχοιτο;</foreign> who would quarrel with <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">a kind host?</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:8:208\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8.208</biblScope> </bibl>; etc.:—<gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"voice\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pass.\">Pass.</a></gram></gramGrp>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">παρ᾽ ἄμμι φιλήσεαι</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">welcome shalt thou be</tr_> in our house, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:1:123\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.123</biblScope></bibl>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:15:281\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">15.281</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"3\" id=\"n110979.2\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> opp. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐρᾶν, τούτους μάλιστά φασι φιλεῖν ὧν ἂν ἐρῶσι</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">regard with affection</tr_> those for whom they have a passion, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0059.tlg012:231c\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Phdr.\">Phdr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">231c</biblScope> </bibl>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὥστε οὐ μόνον φιλοῖο ἄν, ἀλλὰ καὶ ἐρῳ=ο ὑπ᾽ ἀνθρώπων</quote_> <bibl n=\"ur